{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance (or source) and another property on another ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instance (or target)."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Whenever the source property changes, the same value is applied to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"target property; for instance, the following binding:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["  g_object_bind_property (object1, \"property-a\",","                          object2, \"property-b\",","                          G_BINDING_DEFAULT);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"will cause the property named “property-b” of ","type":"text"},{"code":"object2","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to be updated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"every time [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.set"},{"text":"] or the specific accessor changes the value of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the property “property-a” of "},{"code":"object1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to create a bidirectional binding between two properties"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of two ","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances, so that if either property changes, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"other is updated as well, for instance:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["  g_object_bind_property (object1, \"property-a\",","                          object2, \"property-b\",","                          G_BINDING_BIDIRECTIONAL);"],"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"will keep the two properties in sync."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also possible to set a custom transformation function (in both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directions, in case of a bidirectional binding) to apply a custom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"transformation from the source value to the target value before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applying it; for instance, the following binding:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"c","code":["  g_object_bind_property_full (adjustment1, \"value\",","                               adjustment2, \"value\",","                               G_BINDING_BIDIRECTIONAL,","                               celsius_to_fahrenheit,","                               fahrenheit_to_celsius,","                               NULL, NULL);"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"will keep the “value” property of the two adjustments in sync; the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"celsius_to_fahrenheit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function will be called whenever the “value”","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment1"},{"type":"text","text":" changes and will transform the current value"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the property before applying it to the “value” property of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment2"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Vice versa, the "},{"code":"fahrenheit_to_celsius","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function will be called whenever"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the “value” property of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment2"},{"text":" changes, and will transform the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"current value of the property before applying it to the “value” property"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment1"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" does not resolve cycles by itself; a cycle like","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["  object1:propertyA -> object2:propertyB","  object2:propertyB -> object3:propertyC","  object3:propertyC -> object1:propertyA"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"might lead to an infinite loop. The loop, in this particular case,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be avoided if the objects emit the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"text":"notify","type":"text"},{"code":" signal only if the value has effectively been changed. A binding is implemented using the `GObject`notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" signal, so it is susceptible to all the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"various ways of blocking a signal emission, like [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.signal_stop_emission"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.signal_handler_block","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A binding will be severed, and the resources it allocates freed, whenever"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either one of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances it refers to are finalized, or when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding","isActive":true},{"text":" instance loses its last reference.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bindings for languages with garbage collection can use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GObject.Binding.unbind","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] to explicitly release a binding between the source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and target properties, instead of relying on the last reference on the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"binding, source, and target instances to drop."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBinding"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBinding"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"code":"GBinding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingRef"}],"title":"BindingRef","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"BindingRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject10BindingRefV","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure"},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(_:)-4t7wl","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(_:)-76590","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(_:)-791e9","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(_:)-7vk9n","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(_:)-9r2ew","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObj